values:
Yesterday was a really wonderful day! I went to Supanova and hung out most of the day with , who was nice enough to carry all my random bits and pieces, and deal with my never ending whims for photograph taking. There were some definite downsides yesterday, the fact that we stood collectively for over 3 hours in a line, that I was forced to carry my camera on a tripod all day and have to repeatedly set it up to take photographs, the sun was just never in the right place for me to take nice photos, and my wig was the itchiest most annoying POS of all time. Despite all that, it was 100% worth it. I usually don't feel much at Supanova. I just go and enjoy the costumes; the last two years I've been lucky to see two of my all time favourite characters being cosplayed really well but I think if I didn't have that luck, Supanova for me would be a total let down. But this year was pretty amazing I think. It helped that I met a lot of my friends there, both my lolita and university friends. So that was definitely a good thing, and then there's the whole I met Eliza Dushku and got a photo with her! Edit - if the images don't show up: The photos are resized with code, which isn't supported by Internet Explorer. Either open the page using another browser, or go straight to my Photobucket album and view them there. :) Friday Ok, so, to begin. I'll start with Friday cause that was a nice day/night as well. Friday afternoon I drove into the city with my sister and we went shopping for a whole heap of makeup for yesterday and it was an expensive trip. Then after going to 's house to borrow some things, I headed back to meet my sister and my dad for dinner. We ended up going to this really nice Thai restaurant in Darling Harbour, and it was just a really nice, pleasant evening. When I got home I was organising all my stuff for yesterday so I wouldn't have to wake up as early, only to discover that I couldn't find my liquid foundation anywhere. Saturday So, that put a bit of a damper on my morning routine, since I can't really do anything without foundation. Since Sam and I are roughly the same shade of pale, Sam agreed to come over here a little earlier than we thought, which was all dandy but I couldn't really sleep all that well, so I woke up at about 6am, which was really early and got dressed and ended up sitting and twiddling my thumbs for a while, because Sam had overslept and was a little late. Despite the mishap we still made it there on time and met Emma in the insane queue to get inside. We waited in that queue for over an hour until we were finally let inside, we then proceeded to wait in yet another queue to buy the tokens for our photos with Eliza. (See what I mean about waiting in lines).
After that we walked around briefly, and then met some of the other girls outside and had a bit of a chat and photo-session until about 12ish.
This is only a tiny fraction of the line, I think, with a summation of both lines at that time, the line could have easily stretched beyond 2 or 3km. It was insane, I've never been to Supanova and seen it so full!
Here is all of us, we played around a bit with self-timer so I could get into the photo.
Group shot without myself, you can see why the sun was really annoying. It followed us and now half of the girls are in shadow or burnt out. I'm so sorry!
Photo of a photograph being taken, my favourite!
Moved into the shade, to (hopefully) get some better photos!
Some outfit shots :) - I don't know everybody's username, so if you know who they are, comment and I'll edit the post and put your username in.
, ,
Messing about~ and
After that, Sam and I went back inside to get some noms, and Sam wanted to buy some things as well. In the process we ran into , , and .
(more lines and the crowd)
Sorry Tash, but I had to crop you out of the picture cause you were all blurry and out of focus. :( :(
After that, in the food court and the consequent walking around, we ran into some characters from games and movies that I love love love!
FATALITY! (Me with Scorpion from Mortal Kombat)
Thank you Herr Doctor! :D (Medic from TF2)
Belle - Only my favourite Disney Princess ever! And her costume was AMAZING.
I love the Joker and his costume was really good, but I mainly wanted a picture cause I thought the chick was smoking hot. It was about this time, at about 12:45, that we decided to start to line up for my photo with Eliza Dushku. We waited in this line, until probably around 2:30 or 2:45. That's approximately 2 hours of just standing there and waiting. It was intense. But totally freaking worth it, because she was so beautiful and nice. So just to get you in the same mindset as I was.
Ok - so we've all got our faces of pure lust on right now? Exactly how I felt, and what spurred me on in those 2 hours of waiting.
I look like an absolute freak, but she is so so so so beautiful! She asked me if I was dressed up like Bo beep and I just went along with it and was like, rather pathetically and with the testy pop of an 11 year old boy, "sure...!", and she told me that my outfit was amazing, and told me to "Rock on! Represent" and gave me a high 5! So cool, I couldn't even look her in the eye I was so nervous. Guh. So worth it. After having the picture taken, I was very much ready to call it a day. I was exhausted, and my head was itchy and on fire because of my hair. But before we went we ran into some Ghostbusters cosplayers that had Sam quite excited and we got a final shot from the upper level of the whole Dome.
Finally, just as we were leaving. I got a final outfit shot of myself, so that I would have something to upload to Electric Alice Competition like I promised Imogen. The socks were constantly falling down, as evident by this photo. My knees evidently aren't knobbly enough to hold them up! If you like the photo/co-ord, then I'd greatly appreciate it if you could like it on facebook! :)
Click away and check out all the other outfits if you have time!
This has been a mammoth entry. But conventions always are. I'm so sorry that I was so lazy with photo editing. Forgive me!

Dearest Fandom and Friends, In my unending quest to avoid constantly switching between journals and my boundless thirst for an infinite number of icons, I have thus decided it would be the most logical course of action to combine this humble fiction journal together with my personal journal. I feel that I've grown out of my old journal, , and would like to start afresh by using this journal as a platform to a new beginning. I have already posted a Non-Lolita and Lolita photography/image archive from my previous journal, since they're the most important things to keep. Not much else to say, personal entries will be Friends Only and my fiction will remain public; if the people watching my fiction want to see my personal entries, just comment and I shall add you ASAP. Ciao Friendlings! M

SPN joint fic anyone?? I've always wanted to do a joint fic with another writer, I find a long fic very daunting to do and think if there was another person there to motivate me and be a muse, I would find the whole process so much more enjoyable. On that note I'd love to do a Supernatural, Dean/Sam joint fic if anybody would be willing? If you are, maybe just comment on this entry with an example of your favourite work, can be any fandom, just anything that showcases your style of writing. Obviously I'll have to find somebody whose writing style could work well with my own, but that's not too big a deal cause as writers I'm sure we can be flexible! I already have a really vague plot line, but no particulars I'd like to follow, so together I'm sure we could create something beautiful. But anyway, I don't even know if I'll find somebody but I'm hoping!

I recently offered to admin the Supernatural fandom over at my friends community - . I think it's a pretty gee idea, but I'm really bad at advertising and getting people to participate (as you can tell by the 0 comments on the supernatural post). So, if you're a fan of the community, or whatever please help by posting and/or spreading the word about the comm. Thanks pals!
Do EET! ♥

Loyal Followers! This is just a quick note to inform all -3 of you that I have made some changes around this journal. The first and most obvious one is that I've changed the layout - after 2 years of the same one. I can't believe it's been that long! It now delightfully depicts my boys (Dean/Sam from Supernatural) in all their wonderfulness. Please be sure to check it out: . In other organisational news, I have updated the tags system and the dusty archives, so hopefully finding what you want should be a lot easier now. I have even added a post for layouts, as well as co-ordinated my icons to directly link to the fic within that post. Yes, I know, it's all very shiny and amazing. Unfortunately, since I am the actual definition of poverty I've only got 6 icons to work with, so only recurring fandoms have an icon; when I eventually get enough money to support my icon addiction, it will be far cooler. But wait, there's more! New Info section, essentially says same thing as before, just looks nicer. In terms of fics: I have written about half a chapter 12 of Tied to the Wind, will try and have that up at the end of the week (no promises though, since I'm a terrible person like that) and I am hoping to get started on a multi-chaptered Supernatural fic very soon. Though as you all know, I write at about the same speed as a plank of wood so I appreciate your patience. If you've lasted this long, you actually deserve a medal - not even kidding. Anyway, enjoy the changes. M

Since we wrote a list of pet hates, we have decided to write a list about the stuff we love to see in FF. Once again <lj user="visualcomplex"> (<font color="Red">In red</font>) and I in black.

1. unrequited love rocks
<font color="Red">2. love/hate rocks! </font>
3. Long fics with interesting plots
<font color="Red">4. school boys! Slightly rustled up uniforms.</font>
5. Good Smut (one that isnt cliqued or too short)
<font color="Red">6. brotherxbrother love/sex/fluff!!</font>
7. Intricate Characters that are well developed
<font color="Red">8. Original style and well thought out descriptions</font>
9. Relationships that aren't sudden or unrealistic, a chase is there but not one thats been dragged out
<font color="Red">10. Subtle hints</font>
<lj-cut text="The rest under the cut">11. Plots that involve suppressed feelings.... (they usually lead to excellent sex LOL)
<font color="Red">12. REAL tearjerkers.</font>
13. Good humour!!
<font color="Red">14. At the end of the story we want at the very least: a more grudgingly sensitive seme. And a surprisingly tough uke.</font>
15. Love triangles 
<font color="Red">16. Endearingly strong bonds - romantic or boarding.</font>
17. either happy endings or bittersweet. Deaths and other such lame endings SUCK (unless the one who dies is irrelevant and lame)
<font color="Red">18. At least a bit of research before writing </font>
19. A relationship that progresssssesssssss
<font color="Red">20. The most deadly weapon according to Heartbreak.. is not a reaction.. but no reaction at all</font>
21. hawt guys
<font color="Red">22. Regular updates (something that apparently not even the most skilled and tacticful writer can promise...but its nice to have!!)</font>
23. Long and in depth chapters
<font color="Red">24. Self sacrifice without having to use the words "self sacrifice" or suicide (and I mean this in the most subtle and death-evading way..does that make sense?)</font>
25. Really cute first kisses (i'm a sucker for it seriously)
<font color="Red">26. Original (or at the very least.. well thought out) love confession. </font>
<font color="Red">27. A mutual love confession..without having to actually CONFESS</font>
28. Hidden affection from public but they do small things in secret (hold hands under table etc)</lj-cut>

In the spirit of procrastination and my general bad mood, (in red) and I (in black) have compiled a list of things we hate reading in Fanfiction 1. Unrealistic first times 2. OOC aka out of character aka RuinsTheIllusionOfTheCharacterInQuestion 3. MPREG - seriously, WTF? ever heard of adoption? 4. Double U's. aka UBER UKES. lol 5. Crying during a love confession (Crying ukes in general) 6. When "the tongue touches the roof of his mouth" whilst kissing (thats disgusting, seriously T_T) 7. Uke's in dresses. 8. Completely ridiculous overly cliche plots 9. Where the world is openly happy and completely content with gay couples, and every person in the story is gay or openly promiscious 10. Lube. Mood killer. "Do you have anything I can use?" aka "I know youre reallllyyy erect and all but lets stop and have a conversation" 11. Realllllly bad grammar, like a typo here and there is understandable, but where the actual grammar is shocking 12. FF cliche gay marriage. I'm all for it.. as long as it doesn't turn into a QueerAsFolk AU 13. "sasukes POV" and "FLASHBACK" GRRRRRRRRRRRRR I COULDNT HATE ANYTHING MORE!! it's a massive flag that says "I don't know how to write properly" 14. Rasberry talk between lovers. "Shnickerpoos...ookimookidoodle" HELL NO! 15. When the characters share one kiss and all of a sudden they're sex maniacs (where is the transition people!?) 16. What I like to call the "round about." A chase that goes on and on and on and never concludes. By the 30th chapter you start to wonder if soandso will EVER finally make a move with whatshisface. 17. When guy #1 comes and the guy #2 either a) comes at the same time or b) comes immediately after. 18. SPLIT personalities. Unless the character actually DOES have a split personality...stop making him contradict himself. It just doesnt make sense when he dramatically changes his mind back and forth and theres no explaination why. 19. Chapters comprised entirely of dialogue 20. Muscley. Body builder types This list will probably grow XP

Hello everybody! I previously posted my fanfiction at my graphics journal but now I decided it's more practical to seperate these two. And thus this journal was created! Here you will be invited to explore my perverted ramblings. 99.9% of the work found here will be yaoi and shounen ai - that is boy love. I don't really post oneshots but do on occasion - so mostly it will be on-going fics. Warning: The fics I post will more thank likely be of a mature nature, with differing levels of sexual content, violence, language and just general bad-ass stuff. So if such things aren't your style, I advise you turn back now.
